  "prompt": "How do you know if you have a crush on someone?",
  "response": "Recognizing that you have a crush on someone can be both exciting and a bit confusing. Here are some common signs that might indicate you're developing romantic feelings for someone:\n\n1. **Constant Thoughts**:\n   - You find yourself thinking about the person frequently throughout the day.\n   - You're eager to know what they're up to and anticipate your next interaction with them.\n\n2. **Emotional Reactions**:\n   - You feel a surge of happiness or excitement when you're around them or hear from them.\n   - Their mood can influence yours; if they're having a good day, you feel happy too, and vice versa.\n\n3. **Physical Signs**:\n   - You might experience butterflies in your stomach when you see them.\n   - Increased heart rate, nervousness, or even stumbling over your words in their presence.\n\n4. **Desire to Spend Time Together**:\n   - You look for opportunities to be around them, whether it's hanging out in group settings or seeking one-on-one time.\n   - You prioritize activities or occasions where you can connect with them.\n\n5. **Interest in Their Life**:\n   - You're genuinely interested in their hobbies, interests, and personal stories.\n   - You remember small details they've shared and bring them up in conversations.\n\n6. **Jealousy or Protective Feelings**:\n   - You might feel a pang of jealousy if you see them interacting closely with others.\n   - There's a desire to protect or support them in various situations.\n\n7. **Enhanced Attention to Appearance**:\n   - You may find yourself wanting to look your best when you know you'll see them.\n   - Taking extra care in your appearance becomes more important.\n\n8. **Communication Patterns**:\n   - You initiate conversations more often, whether through text, calls, or in person.\n   - You feel excited to respond to their messages and prolong conversations.\n\n9. **Future Thinking**:\n   - You start imagining or daydreaming about future scenarios involving them.\n   - Considering them in your plans, even in small ways, indicates deeper feelings.\n\n10. **Physical Closeness**:\n    - You seek subtle ways to be physically closer, such as sitting next to them or finding excuses for light touches.\n   \n**What to Do If You Think You Have a Crush:**\n\n- **Self-Reflection**: Take some time to understand your feelings. Journaling can help clarify your emotions.\n- **Observe Their Behavior**: Sometimes, mutual interest can be a good indicator. Notice how they act around you compared to others.\n- **Talk to Friends**: Sharing your feelings with trusted friends can provide perspective and support.\n- **Decide on Next Steps**: If you feel comfortable, consider expressing your feelings to them. Whether it's through a conversation or subtle gestures, communication can help clarify the situation.\n\nRemember, having a crush is a natural and common experience. It's a part of forming meaningful connections and understanding your own emotions better. Whatever you decide to do, prioritize your emotional well-being and approach the situation with honesty and kindness.",
